Here we have the third, or perhaps the fourth lesson on this site from the &quot;Doc Spatz School of Charm.&quot;<br><br>
...AKA...<br><br>
How to swing from &quot;Vald the Impailer&quot; to &quot;Mother Theresa&quot; with the flick of a mental switch, and then think that everyone will just conveniently forget the recent projectile display of venom and torture so we can just start the process all over again.<br><br>
In my back yard there are old stone walls inhabited with many snakes. They serve a very good purpose in those walls by consuming many insects, a job for which I respect them. Every so often, I come across freshly shed snake skins. Does this mean the snakes have packed up and left? No, there has been no transformation. They are still snakes still doing what snakes do best. The old stone walls? Well, they just sit there, doing what they do best. <br><br>
I recommend, instead, &quot;The Viet Cong School of Charm&quot;. You know right up front with what you are dealing, and with unswerving consistancy, too!<br><br>
...and boy, do I have a deal for you!
